        "1026-43-f-1-iv-Interp-1": [
            {
                "action": "POST", 
                "node": {
                    "children": [], 
                    "label": [
                        "1026", 
                        "43", 
                        "f", 
                        "1", 
                        "iv", 
                        "Interp", 
                        "1"
                    ], 
                    "node_type": "interp", 
                    "text": "1. Scheduled payments. Under \u00a7 1026.43(f)(1)(iv)(A), the legal obligation must provide that scheduled payments must be substantially equal and determined using an amortization period that does not exceed 30 years. Balloon payments often result when the periodic payment would fully repay the loan amount only if made over some period that is longer than the loan term. For example, a loan term of 10 years with periodic payments based on an amortization period of 20 years would result in a balloon payment being due at the end of the loan term. Whatever the loan term, the amortization period used to determine the scheduled periodic payments that the consumer must pay under the terms of the legal obligation may not exceed 30 years."
                }
            }
        ], 
        "1026-43-f-1-iv-Interp-2": [
